The state capture inquiry, headed by deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo, is looking into allegations of state capture at SAA. JOHANNESBURG - The head of department for procurement at South African Airways (SAA) Technica Nontsasa Memela is continuing with her testimony at the state capture inquiry on Friday. The inquiry, headed by deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo, is looking into allegations of state capture at SAA. WATCH: SAA Technical procurement head in state capture hot seat 